{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}{\f2\fnil \fcharset2 WingDings;}{\f3\fnil \fcharset0 Arial;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <BM 3>\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b  TPJHotLabel
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Heirachy\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Properties\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Methods\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Events\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f0\fs24\cf3\b 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 This component provides a clickable label that can accessed a user-defined URL when clicked\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Unit\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 PJHotLabel\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Use this component when you need a label that can be clicked to access a URL using the default browser or email client.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 In addition to the properties of \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 TLabel\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 , from which this component descends, it provides all additional properties for working with URLs. The effect of some of TLabel's properties is modified in TPJHotLabel.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 9>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 URL\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 9>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property is used for storing the URL to be accessed and the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 10>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Caption\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 10>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property can either store descriptive text or can reflect the URL, depending on the value of the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 11>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 CaptionIsURL\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 11>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property. When the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 12>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ValidateURL\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 12>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 , URLs areautomatically validated, raising an exception if invalid.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The label's \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 13>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Font\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 13>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property defaults to a font based on the parent font at the time the component is dropped on the form, but coloured navy blue. It should be noted that the Font property does not automatically reflect changes in the parent controls's font since \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 14>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ParentFont\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 14>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  defaults to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i False\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 . The label can be highlighted when the mouse passes over it. It does this if the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 15>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 HighlightURL\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 15>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 , in which case the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 16>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 HighlightFont\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 16>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property is used when the mouse is over the label. The HighlightFont is, by default, based on the default font used by the Font property, but with a different colour. A special "hand point" cursor is used by default when the mouse is over the label. accordingly the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 17>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Cursor\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 17>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property defaults to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i crHandPoint\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  rather than \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i crDefault\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 .
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Useful,customisable, pop-up hints can be displayed when the mouse cursor hovers over the label. You can either display text from the Hint property as normal, display the URL (useful when the URL is not displayed in the label) or customise the hint each time it is displayed. The \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 18>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 HintStyle\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 18>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property is used to determine how hints are handled and custom hints are set up by handling the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 19>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OnCustomHint\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 19>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  event.
\par \plain\f1\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b Backwards Compatibility\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The component is backward compatible with v1 of the component and, by default, behaves similarly. The effect of this is that some new features are switched off by default. In particular:
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 CaptionIsURL defaults to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  because the v1 component had no URL property and the URL was stored in the Caption property and always displayed in the component.
\par \pard \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 HighlightURL defaults to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i False\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  because highlighting was not supported in the v1 component.
\par \pard \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Customisable hints were not available so HintStyle defaults to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i hsNormal\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 , which uses the Hint property for the pop-up hint text.
\par \pard \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Font is set to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i clNavy\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  by default and ParentFont is therefore \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i False\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 .
\par \pard \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \tab Although Cursor defaults to \plain\f3\fs18\cf2\i crHandPoint\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  a constant named \plain\f3\fs18\cf2\i crHand\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  is also supplied since this was the name used for the "hand" cursor used in v1.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par }

