\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 A TPJHotLabel can highlight its text when the mouse passes over the control\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  The font that is used to highlight the text is determined by the HighlightFont property. The property defaults to the same font as the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Font\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property but with the colour changed to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i clRed\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 .
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Note that the highlighting only takes place when the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 HighlightURL\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 .
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 It is recommended that only the colour and some styles of the font are altered and the font size and name remain unchanged so that the label does not grow and shrink when the cursor passes over it. See the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 example\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  for details of two suitable designs.
\par 
\par 
\par }

