\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b TPJHotLabel.\plain\f1\fs22\cf3\b HintStyle\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b 
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJHotLabel\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Determines the source of the text displayed in the component's hint.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \pard \fi-200 \li200 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b type\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  TPJHLHintStyle = (hsNormal, hsURL, hsCustom);
\par \pard \plain\f3\fs8\cf2\b 
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf1\b \protect <KP 3>\plain\f3\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 HintStyle\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 : \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 TPJHLHintStyle\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 ;\plain\f3\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The HintStyle property determines how the text used in the component's hint is derived. There are three possible sources of the of the hint text:
\par 
\par \pard \fi-1400 \li1400 \tx1400 \plain\f1\fs18\cf1\i \protect <BD 10>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i Style\tab Notes\plain\f1\fs18\cf1\i \protect </BD 10>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i 
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2  
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i hsNormal\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab The pop-up hint displays as normal - i.e. the hint's text is taken from the Hint property.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i hsURL\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab The pop-up hint displays the URL property value. The Hint property is ignored.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i hsCustom\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 \tab The use can specify a custom hint by handling the OnCustomHint event. See the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OnCustomHint\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  topic for details of how the hint is set. If the OnCustomHint is not handled then the hint's text comes from the Hint property as normal.
\par \pard \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <BD 9>\plain\f1\fs12\cf2  \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </BD 9>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par Note that no pop-up hint will display unless hints are enabled using either the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ShowHint\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property or the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ParentShowHint\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  and its parent's ShowHint property is also \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 .\plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The default value of HintStyle is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i hsNormal\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 .\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par }

