\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Determines where a control looks for its font information.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 3>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 ParentFont\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 : \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 Boolean\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ;\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 To have the component use the same font in its \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Font\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property as its parent control, set ParentFont to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 .
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Normally ParentFont is set to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  for all controls in order to ensure that all the controls on a form have a uniform appearance. For example, if ParentFont is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  for all controls in a form, changing the form's Font property to 12-point Courier causes all controls on the form to use that font.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 To specify a different font for a particular control, change the control's Font property, and ParentFont becomes \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i False\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  automatically.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The ParentFont property of TPJHotLabel defaults to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i False\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  since the default attributes of the Font property differs from the parent to make the hot-link stand out.\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par }

