{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}{\f2\fmodern Courier New;}{\f3\fmodern \fcharset0 Courier New;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b TPJHotLabel.\plain\f1\fs22\cf3\b URL\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b 
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJHotLabel\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Stores the URL that is to be accessed when the label is clicked\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 3>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 URL\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 : \plain\f3\fs18\cf2\b string\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ;\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Use the URL property to record the URL that is to be displayed when the label is clicked\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  The default web browser or mail client are executed to action the URL.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 If the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ValidateURL\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  then any URL assigned to the property must be valid or a \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 9>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 EPJURLError\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 9>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  exception will be raised.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 When the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 CaptionIsURL\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  then any URL assigned to the URL property is also assigned to the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 10>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Caption\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 10>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property and displayed in the label. This makes it easy to display the URL in the label by assigning just one property.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The URL's value can be displayed in the label's \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Hint\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property by setting the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 HintStyle\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i hsURL\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 .
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The default value of the URL property is: \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i http://localhost/\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par }

