\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b TPJHotLabel.\plain\f1\fs22\cf3\b ValidateURL\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b 
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJHotLabel\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Determines whether the URL stored in the component is validated or not\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 3>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 ValidateURL\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 : \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 Boolean\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ;\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Set this property to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  to cause any value assigned to the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 URL\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property to be validated when assigned to the property. When ValidateURL is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i False\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  no URLs are validated. Note that setting this property to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  causes the current URL to be validated.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 URLs are validated only by examining the protocol and checking it is supported. Valid protocols are:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li800 \tx400 \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 \tab http://
\par \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 \tab https://
\par \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 \tab mailto:
\par \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 \tab file:
\par \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 \tab ftp://
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f5\fs18\cf2 If validation fails a \plain\f5\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 EPJURLError\plain\f5\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f5\fs18\cf2  exception is raised. If this exception is raised while setting ValidateURL to \plain\f5\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f5\fs18\cf2  the default URL is stored in the URL property.
\par \plain\f5\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f5\fs18\cf2 When the \plain\f5\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 CaptionIsURL\plain\f5\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f5\fs18\cf2  and ValidateURL properties are both \plain\f5\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 , assigning text to the \plain\f5\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 8>\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 Caption\plain\f5\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 8>\plain\f5\fs18\cf2  property also causes the text to be validated. The is because setting the Caption property in this case automatically updates the URL property.
\par \plain\f5\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f5\fs18\cf2 The default value is \plain\f5\fs18\cf2\i True\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 .\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par }

