\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b TPJHotLabel.\plain\f1\fs22\cf3\b OnCustomHint\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b 
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJHotLabel\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Example\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 An event that enables the user to specify a custom hint to be displayed by the component\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par 
\par \pard \fi-200 \li200 \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b type \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 TPJHLCustomHintEvent = \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b procedure\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 (Sender: TObject; \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b var\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  HintStr: \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b string\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ) \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b of object\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ;
\par \pard \plain\f3\fs8\cf2\b 
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 OnCustomHint\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 : \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 TPJHLCustomHintEvent\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 ;\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 This event is triggered only when the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 HintStyle\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property is set to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i hsCustom\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  and a hint is about to be displayed\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  Handling the event enables the user to specify the text that is displayed in the pop-up hint. The event handler is passed the current \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Hint\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property value in the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i HintStr\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  parameter. Specify the hint text by setting \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i HintStr\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  to the required value.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 If HintStyle is \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\i hsCustom\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  and the event is not handled then the value of the Hint property is displayed as normal.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 See the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 example\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  for one possible use of the OnCustomHint event.\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par }

