{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}{\f2\fnil \fcharset0 Courier New;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b Example\plain\f1\fs22\cf3\b  2\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b :\plain\f1\fs22\cf3\b  Using the OnCustomHint event\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 1>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 These examples show how to use the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OnCustomHint\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  event of \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 TPJHotLabel\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 . We handle the event to display a hint containing some descriptive text and the URL in brackets.
\par \plain\f1\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b Example 1\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Drop a TPJHotLabel component on a form and create a FormCreate and a OnCustomHint event handler, completed as follows:
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf1\b \protect <KP 2>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b procedure\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  TForm1.FormCreate(Sender: TObject);
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b begin\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 
\par   PJHotLabel1.URL := 'http://www.delphidabbler.com/';
\par   PJHotLabel1.HintStyle := hsCustom;
\par   PJHotLabel1.ShowHint := True;
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b end\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ;
\par \plain\f2\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b procedure\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  TForm1.PJHotLabel1CustomHint(Sender: TObject;
\par   \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b var\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  HintStr: \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b String\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 );
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b begin\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 
\par   HintStr := Format('View the site''s index page (%s)', 
\par     [PJHotLabel1.URL]);
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b end\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ;\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b Example 2\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 This example is similar to the first example except we store the custom hint text in the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Hint\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property rather than entering the text in the form unit. This keeps the form's text in the form file. Drop a TPJHotLabel component on a form and create a FormCreate and a OnCustomHint event handler, as before, and comple them as follows:
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf1\b \protect <KP 3>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b procedure\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  TForm1.FormCreate(Sender: TObject);
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b begin
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2   PJHotLabel1.Hint := 'View the site''s index page (%s)';
\par   PJHotLabel1.URL := 'http://www.delphidabbler.com/';
\par   PJHotLabel1.HintStyle := hsCustom;
\par   PJHotLabel1.ShowHint := True;
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b end\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ;
\par \plain\f2\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b procedure\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  TForm1.PJHotLabel1CustomHint(Sender: TObject;
\par   \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b var\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  HintStr: \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b String\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 );
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b begin\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 
\par   HintStr := Format(HintStr, [PJHotLabel1.URL]);
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2\b end\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 ;\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par }

